          "32593",
          "7 courses in OULAD",
          "VLE logs",
          "[id_student, code_module_student_presentation, sum_click, date_unregistration, final_score, studied_credits, Module_presentation_length, date_registration, imd_band, code_module_presentation, region, num_of_prev_attempts, code_module, highest_education, cohort, disability, code_presentation, age_band, count_click]",
          "End of Course",
          "Filling of missing values takes advantage of the sequential nature of the data. If a point is missing at moment V, it is filled using an “average” of V at t-1 and V at t+1. \n\nAdditionally, the authors address the class imbalance by using ISMOTE - which tests generated samples and decides on whether the generated sample should be accepted or not. \n\nThe sequences are given as input to 2 distinct modules simultaneously: a teacher model which uses Attention Layers into a Bi-Directional LSTM Network (which is pre-trained). There is also a Student Model that uses a CNN-based ResNet-101.",
          "CNN, Bi-LSTM, LSTM, ResNet, EDL_KDF",
          "Holdout Method",
          "{Accuracy: 0.996 - EDF_KDF, Precision: 0.9921 - EDF_KDF, Recall: 0.9921 - EDF_KDF, AUC: 0.99 - EDF_KDF}",
          "Authors propose a new DL model for the prediction of student performance. \n\nThe model uses 2 distinct Deep Learning modules for the prediction of student performance. Results are very high in comparison with other alternative models in the literature.",
          "- Holdout Method\n\n- Unspecified Train/Test separation\n\n- It seems, from description, that final score is used as an input to the model."
        ]
      ],
      "index": 7
    }
